  exit(1);
}
```

The issue is on line 51: `if (strcmp(f->type[i], type)) break;`

When the field name matches but the type doesn't match, the code breaks out of the loop but then falls through to the error handling code. However, the loop index `i` is still set to the mismatched field's index. If there are multiple fields with the same name but different types, this could cause the function to return an incorrect field index instead of continuing to search for a proper match.

According to the PR description, the fix should change this to:
```c
if (!strcmp(f->type[i], type))
  return i;
```

This way, it only returns `i` when both the name matches AND the type matches. If the type doesn't match, it continues searching through the remaining fields.

