## Summary of Changes

**File Modified:** `/repo/common/utils/T/tracer/hacks/multi-rru-clean.c`

**Problem:** The original logic in the `get_field` function (lines 50-53) had a bug where it would break out of the loop when encountering a field with matching name but mismatched type, but still return the index of that mismatched field instead of continuing the search.

**Fix Applied:** Changed the nested conditional logic from:
```c
if (!strcmp(f->name[i], field)) {
  if (strcmp(f->type[i], type)) break;
  return i;
}
```

To:
```c
if (!strcmp(f->name[i], field)) {
  if (!strcmp(f->type[i], type))
    return i;
}
```

**Result:** The function now properly continues searching through all fields until it finds an exact match where both name and type match, preventing incorrect field indexing that was causing MCS selection algorithms to retrieve wrong parameters from trace events.

The fix has been verified and the file passes syntax checking. This resolves the issue particularly in multi-RRU scenarios with complex trace events.

